7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Adobe Podcast and Podcastle share a solid foundation of core features including Speech To Text, Noise Removal, Podcast Editing. On the other hand, Podcastle uniquely offers Text To Speech and Voice Cloning and Custom Voices, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Adobe Podcast holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Podcastle scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Adobe Podcast offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $0, compared to Podcastle's starting price of $11.99/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Adobe Podcast's free tier and Podcastle's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
